description: This course will include the major topics of cell biology and microbiology that are foundational for an understanding of normal and pathological cellular processes. Topics will include the study of prokaryotic and eukaryotic cell structures and functions, the main biological molecules, membrane transport, cellular communications, the flow of genetic information, cell division, and cellular metabolism. The context for this course will be the application of cell biology to understanding the cellular basis of human diseases and the role of genetics and genomics in health and disease processes.
name: CELL BIOLOGY
